  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation Examples:\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- United Kingdom: Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Canada: Proceeds of Crime (Money Laundering) and Terrorist Financing Act\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Enhanced background checks\n- Mandatory record-keeping\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Financial regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
